The paper presents a general approach to learning the structure of causal models based on d-separation constraints, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of Boolean satisfiability (SAT) solver is also a common technique in computer science and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the effect of assumptions on discovery, which is related to data mining (cs.DM) and statistical inference (cs.SI).
